result.execSummary:
The defendant Darius Laronte Latham was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Darius Laronte Latham is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Darius Laronte Latham was found guilty of Possess Firearm-Adjudicated Deliquent of a Felony, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(1m)(bm).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Defendant Darius Laronte Latham in court, in custody.  Attorney Michael B Plaisted in court for Darius Laronte Latham.  Attorney Dennis Patrick Murphy in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for sentencing.  Court found the State has satisfied victims' rights law. Statements made by the State, Defense Counsel, and Defendant.

AS TO COUNT 6:
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 2 YEARS, CONCURRENT to sentence in case #21CF4901; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 1 YEAR; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 1 YEAR. 

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 3 YEARS. 

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION IF REVOKED: 
- Provide DNA sample.
- Full-time work/school (minimum of 20 hours of work per week if in school). 
- Obtain HS diploma/HSED/GED.  
- Obtain a valid driver's license. 
- Complete 8 hours of in person driver's education. 
- Complete a cognitive thinking program. 

Court ordered the defendant to pay the DNA surcharge by the end of supervision. Failure to pay shall result in a civil judgment. Court waived all other court costs, fees, and surcharges due to a finding of indigency. 
 If revoked, Court ordered that the DNA surcharge be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections in an amount or percentage the Department (DOC) determines to be reasonable and as a condition of extended supervision.  DOC shall collect those sums. Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.

20 day appeal rights given. Voting and firearm warnings given.

Defendant Darius Laronte Latham in court, in custody.  Attorney Michael B Plaisted in court for Darius Laronte Latham.  Attorney Dennis Patrick Murphy in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for global resolution with case #21CF4901.  Parties have reached an agreement.  Plea negotiations set forth on the record and agreed upon by the parties.

AS TO COUNT 6:
Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Defendant further advised that if not a US citizen, deportation is possible. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, Addendum, and Elements/Jury Instructions received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Pursuant to plea negotiations and on the motion of the State, Court ordered COUNTS 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 7, and 8 DISMISSED.  

Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon, he may never own or possess a firearm.  Court advised defendant that he may not vote until his civil rights have been restored.  Case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 40.
